  <discussion>Didymodon asperifolius can sometimes be immediately recognized by a red-yellow
        translucency in leaves of dry plants, like oiled paper. The adaxial surface of the costa may
        have either quadrate or short-rectangular cells. The distal laminal cells are also rather
        large for the genus. The KOH reaction, as well as the natural color of the lamina are
        sometimes light orange, but usually quite red. Some plants may appear green but the laminal
        cell walls are red under high magnification.</discussion>
